    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Panel on Problems at Walter Reed Issues Strong Rebuke'' (news article, April 12):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Panel on Problems at Walter Reed Issues Strong Rebuke'' (news article, April 12):</p>
        <p>Every patriotic American will want to endorse the recommendations of the West-Marsh Independent Review Group regarding Walter Reed Army Medical Center.</p>
        <p>Of course, the continuing challenge for our country is to channel all the anger and anguish we still feel about the way that some of our brave heroes were treated into a clear prescription for positive change.</p>
        <p>Paralyzed Veterans of America estimates that there is a medical care financing gap of $2.1 billion between what the administration has proposed and what is needed to strengthen veterans' health care for the coming year.</p>
        <p>And there's a second gap in excess of $1 billion to upgrade facilities.</p>
        <p>The administration and Congress must close these financing gaps today and ensure that they remain closed in the future.</p>
        <p>Louis Irvin  Executive Director  Paralyzed Veterans of America  Washington, April 16, 2007</p>
      </block>
